cs.LG, cs.BE, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.CV 

The paper discusses the use of support vector machines for classification of human ECGs, which is a problem in machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves signal processing and analysis, which could fall under cs.BE (Bioengineering), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SI (Signal Processing). Finally, the use of Fourier magnitude spectra and lower dimensional projections could also involve computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category.
